(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
examined the 
<typeStatus id="54A58873FFAB765BFD12D24A48CCF33D" box="[697,760,1554,1575]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFF04D2684B82F35F" authorityName="Crosby" authorityYear="1905" box="[175,438,1584,1605]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alascensis">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFF04D2684B82F35F" box="[175,438,1584,1605]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Oedothorax alascensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in NMNH and found them identical with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFEFFD2164AE0F399" authority="(Chamberlin, 1920)" baseAuthorityName="Chamberlin" baseAuthorityYear="1920" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Collinsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="clypiella">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFEFFD2164876F379" box="[340,578,1614,1635]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Collinsia clypiella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFDF1D2164AFFF398" author="Chamberlin RV" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="193 - 201" refId="ref89702" refString="Chamberlin RV. 1920. New spiders from Utah. The Canadian Entomologist 52: 193 - 201." type="journal article" year="1920">Chamberlin, 1920</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFEBCD23548C1F399" authority="(Chamberlin, 1949)" baseAuthorityName="Chamberlin" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[279,757,1645,1667]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Collinsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stylifera">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFEBCD2354BC3F398" box="[279,503,1645,1666]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Collinsia stylifera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFDA0D23548DDF398" author="Chamberlin RV" box="[523,745,1645,1667]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="483 - 562" refId="ref89721" refString="Chamberlin RV. 1949. On some American spiders of the family Erigonidae. Annals of the Entomological Society of America 41: 483 - 562." type="journal article" year="1949">Chamberlin, 1949</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The synonymization of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFE03D2D44827F3BB" box="[424,531,1676,1697]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Collinsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFE03D2D44827F3BB" box="[424,531,1676,1697]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Collinsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFDFAD2D448F0F3BB" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1911" box="[593,708,1676,1697]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Halorates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFDFAD2D448F0F3BB" box="[593,708,1676,1697]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Halorates</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFE8DD2F24BEDF3DB" author="Millidge AF" box="[294,473,1706,1729]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref93539" refString="Millidge AF. 1977. The conformation of the male palpal organs of linyphiid spiders, and its application to the taxonomic and phylogenetic analysis of the family (Araneae: Linyphiidae). Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society 4: 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="1977">Millidge (1977)</bibRefCitation>
based on similarities in their palpal structure, but it was rejected by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFD1AD2914AEFF3E4" author="Eskov KY" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="287 - 298" refId="ref90697" refString="Eskov KY. 1990. The spider genus Collinsia O. Pickard- Cambridge 1913 in the fauna of Siberia and the Soviet Far East (Arachnida: Araneae: Linyphiidae). Senckenbergiana Biologica 70: 287 - 298." type="journal article" year="1990">Eskov (1990)</bibRefCitation>
based on differences in their chaetotaxy and palpal features. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFEF9D35E480DF207" author="Buckle D &amp; Carroll D &amp; Crawford R &amp; Roth V" box="[338,569,1798,1821]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="89 - 191" refId="ref89563" refString="Buckle D, Carroll D, Crawford R, Roth V. 2001. Linyphiidae and Pimoidae of America north of Mexico: checklist, synonymy, and literature. Fabreries, Supplement 10: 89 - 191." type="journal article" year="2001">
Buckle 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFE00D35F4BD2F201" box="[427,486,1798,1820]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
, however, found that the differences cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFE7DD37D485EF221" author="Eskov KY" box="[470,618,1829,1851]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="287 - 298" refId="ref90697" refString="Eskov KY. 1990. The spider genus Collinsia O. Pickard- Cambridge 1913 in the fauna of Siberia and the Soviet Far East (Arachnida: Araneae: Linyphiidae). Senckenbergiana Biologica 70: 287 - 298." type="journal article" year="1990">Eskov (1990)</bibRefCitation>
did not hold for the 
<typeStatus id="54A58873FFAB765BFF4DD31C4B2CF243" box="[230,280,1860,1881]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">type</typeStatus>
species of these two genera, and that the difference in chaetotaxy was not greater than found within a number of currently accepted genera. Based on these reasons, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFC47D55A4EF4F403" author="Buckle D &amp; Carroll D &amp; Crawford R &amp; Roth V" box="[1004,1216,258,281]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="89 - 191" refId="ref89563" refString="Buckle D, Carroll D, Crawford R, Roth V. 2001. Linyphiidae and Pimoidae of America north of Mexico: checklist, synonymy, and literature. Fabreries, Supplement 10: 89 - 191." type="journal article" year="2001">
Buckle 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFB95D55B4E40F40D" box="[1086,1140,258,280]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
accepted 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFA87D55A4976F42D" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFA87D55A4FA5F40D" box="[1324,1425,258,279]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Collinsia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Collinsia</taxonomicName>
as
</emphasis>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFB96D5794E9AF42C" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1911" box="[1085,1198,289,310]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Halorates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFB96D5794E9AF42C" box="[1085,1198,289,310]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Halorates</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, based on the synapomorphies proposed for the re-delimited 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFC82D506499EF469" authorityName="Triceps Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[809,938,350,371]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC82D506499EF469" box="[809,938,350,371]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the present study, and the differences in the pedipalp of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFC78D5254EFDF488" authorityName="Crosby" authorityYear="1905" box="[979,1225,381,402]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alascensis">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC78D5254EFDF488" box="[979,1225,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Oedothorax alascensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
depicted in figure 
<quantity id="4CE69B34FFAB765BFC82D5C4496CF4A8" box="[809,856,412,434]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFCC9D5C44E36F4A8" author="Banks N" box="[866,1026,412,434]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="477 - 486" refId="ref88617" refString="Banks N, 1900. Arachnida of the expedition. In: Papers from the Harriman Alaska Expedition. XI. Entomological results: 5 Arachnida. Proceedings of the Washington Academy of Sciences 2: 477 - 486." type="journal article" year="1900">Banks (1900)</bibRefCitation>
, this species does seemingly not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFC3FD5E24E21F4D5" authorityName="Triceps Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[916,1045,442,463]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC3FD5E24E21F4D5" box="[916,1045,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, we accept the transfer of this species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FFAB765BFC4DD5814E67F4F4" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1911" box="[998,1107,473,494]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Halorates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFC4DD5814E67F4F4" box="[998,1107,473,494]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">Halorates</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B20FFAB765BFBD0D5814F65F4F5" author="Buckle D &amp; Carroll D &amp; Crawford R &amp; Roth V" box="[1147,1361,473,495]" pageId="118" pageNumber="535" pagination="89 - 191" refId="ref89563" refString="Buckle D, Carroll D, Crawford R, Roth V. 2001. Linyphiidae and Pimoidae of America north of Mexico: checklist, synonymy, and literature. Fabreries, Supplement 10: 89 - 191." type="journal article" year="2001">
Buckle 
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FFAB765BFB65D5824F31F4F4" box="[1230,1285,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="535">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
